! Single-phase exponential (CVR) load — power-flow comparison case.
!
! Topology: src ──[1-ph line, 0.5 km]── lb   (earth return, no explicit neutral)
!
! Exponential load with non-integer P exponent and a distinct Q exponent:
!   P = P0·v^1.4   (CVRwatts = gamma_p)
!   Q = Q0·v^2.0   (CVRvars  = gamma_q)   with v = |V|/Vnom
! OpenDSS model=4 (exponential/CVR). Vminpu=0 Vmaxpu=2 disable the constant-Z
! fallback so the power law holds across the whole operating range.
!
! The non-integer P exponent routes through BMOPF's genuinely nonlinear power
! term (not the quadratic Z/I/P shortcut), and the distinct gamma_q exercises
! the reactive exponential path against an OpenDSS baseline.

Clear

New Circuit.pf_exp_1ph basekv=0.240 pu=1.0 angle=0 phases=1 bus1=src.1.0 model=ideal

New Line.l1 bus1=src.1 bus2=lb.1 phases=1 length=0.5 units=km r1=0.5 x1=0.2

New Load.ld1 bus1=lb.1 phases=1 kv=0.240 kw=15 kvar=5 model=4 CVRwatts=1.4 CVRvars=2.0 Vminpu=0 Vmaxpu=2

Set VoltageBases=[0.240]
CalcVoltageBases
Solve
